    {
      "id": "cfc07f41e7b94883815e393589385104e1f39825",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-10-14 16:55:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nCould you please provide some sample output from the catalog list command and see if it is OK for Mike Stok and John Spray. The output needs to be proper YAML format.  It wouldn't hurt to include this in the commit comment as well. \n\nFor easier parsing,I think it should be a single word before the colon (e.g. \"catalog:\" or \"log:\").\n\nDid you test this with \"lctl --device MGS llog_catlist\"?  For this patch there should probably be a couple of test cases added to conf-sanity.sh to ensure this code works correctly in the future.\n\nThe other new functionality that needs to be added (in a separate patch) is the ability to dump an MGS config log in userspace in YAML format. Currently it is either possible to dump the config log to the console in a random format, or just a list of records to userspace without any of th contents.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
